• Backend Agent

  Role: Senior backend gameplay systems engineer for RiskArena.

  Goal:
  Implement the backend foundation for a unified Items system with L2-
  style enchanting for owned weapon and armor copies.

  Product direction locked:
  - Items navigation in frontend will become a unified hub with:
    - Loadout
    - Shop
    - Upgrade
  - Enchanting applies only to:
    - weapon
    - armor
  - Ability items are not enchantable for now

  Existing design constraints:
  - Tiers: Common -> Uncommon -> Rare -> Epic -> Legendary
  - Every class has a full set for every tier:
    - weapon
    - armor
    - ability
  - Shop sells: Common, Uncommon, Rare
  - Epic and Legendary are reward/drop-only
  - Duplicates are allowed
  - Only one equipped item per slot
  - Epic and Legendary can have item-specific passives
  - Backend is authoritative for all combat-impacting values

  Important identity contract:
  - `inventory_id` = unique owned copy
  - `item_id` = catalog item definition
  - Enchanting must be stored and resolved per owned copy, not per catalog
  item

  What to implement:

  1. Schema/data model
  - Extend the current item/inventory model to support enchanting
  - Add per-inventory enchant tracking
  - Add support for scroll ownership/counts in the simplest robust way
  that fits the current architecture
  - Keep migration changes additive and safe for existing DBs

  2. Enchanting rules
  Implement L2-style enchanting for owned copies.

  Enchantable:
  - weapon
  - armor

  Not enchantable:
  - ability
  - consumables

  Max enchant:
  - Common: +5
  - Uncommon: +6
  - Rare: +8
  - Epic: +10
  - Legendary: +12

  Safe thresholds:
  - Common / Uncommon / Rare: safe through +3
  - Epic / Legendary: safe through +2

  Scroll types:
  - normal_scroll
  - blessed_scroll

  Normal scroll:
  - success guaranteed up to safe threshold
  - above safe threshold, success chance decreases by current enchant
  level
  - failure above safe threshold destroys the item copy and removes it
  from inventory

  Blessed scroll:
  - usable on the same enchantable items
  - on failure, item is not destroyed
  - MVP failure behavior: enchant stays unchanged

  3. Success chance model
  - Implement a clear backend probability table or deterministic chance
  mapping by:
    - item tier
    - current enchant level
    - scroll type
  - Keep it simple and easy to rebalance later

  4. Scroll economy
  - Add backend support for scroll ownership/consumption
  - Normal scrolls should be obtainable via shop
  - Blessed scrolls should be rarer/premium-ready
  - Do not implement crafting or broader upgrade systems

  5. Combat integration
  Apply enchant bonuses automatically in backend combat calculations.

  Recommended effect model:
  - weapon enchant increases attack scaling, and optionally small ability
  scaling where appropriate
  - armor enchant increases hp scaling and/or survivability scaling
  - final combat stats should include:
    - class bonuses
    - equipped base item stats
    - passive effects
    - enchant bonuses

  Apply where relevant:
  - arena combat
  - boss calculations where item modifiers already matter

  6. API support
  Add/adjust endpoints for:
  - fetching upgrade/enchantable inventory state
  - fetching scroll availability
  - performing enchant attempts
  - returning result payloads for success/failure/destruction
  - validating ownership, item slot, class restrictions if relevant, max
  cap, and scroll availability

  Use atomic transactions for enchant attempts.

  7. Duplicate handling
  - Duplicates remain allowed
  - Enchant level belongs to the specific owned copy
  - Destroying one copy must not affect duplicates
  - Equipped copy replacement logic must remain correct

  8. Tests
  Add focused tests for:
  - per-copy enchant isolation
  - max enchant cap
  - safe-threshold guaranteed success
  - normal scroll destruction failure
  - blessed scroll non-destruction failure
  - scroll consumption
  - invalid item/slot handling
  - combat modifier integration from enchant
  - transaction safety / ownership checks

  Constraints:
  - No frontend implementation here
  - No unrelated feature work
  - No marketplace/NFT/crafting
  - No enchanting for ability items
  - Keep changes pragmatic and testable

  Deliverables:
  - schema/model updates
  - enchant backend endpoints
  - combat integration
  - tests
  - summary of touched files
  - short contract note for frontend

